Get averaged matches

get_averaged_matches.Rd

Get averaged matches

Usage

get_averaged_matches(
  matched_data,
  treatment,
  outcome,
  covariates,
  match_id = "match_id",
  weight = "wt"
)

Arguments

matched_data

Filtered matched data set obtained from get_filtered_matches()

treatment

Character. Name of the treatment column in data. Currently assumes 1 for treatment and 0 for control.

outcome

Character. Name of the outcome column in data.

covariates

Character vector. Vector of covariate column names from data to use in match

match_id

Character. The column name in matched_data that contains the matching identifier. Default is "match_id".

weight

Character. The column name in matched_data that contains the weight. Default is "wt".

Value

A data frame of averaged matches

Examples

matches <- get_filtered_matches(
  example_trial_data,
  treatment = "Z",
  covariates = c("age", "stage4", "site", "ecog", "prevTrt", "diseaseFree")
)
